show_title: Clanker Gets Acquired, Memes Get Unleashed: GM Farcaster ep303 with @dwr and @dish
text:
We‚Äôre excited to share that Clanker is joining Farcaster! 

Clanker is the leading launchpad on Base and home to projects like Bankr, Noice, Bracky and more. We‚Äôre thrilled to join forces to make it easier for everyone to create and participate in onchain communities. We plan to integrate Clanker more deeply into the app. More on this soon.

We have a few updates for the Clanker ecosystem:

1. Starting today, Clanker protocol fees will be used to buy and hold $CLANKER.

2. Clanker v0 through v3.1 collected a portion of protocol fees in ecosystem tokens into a fee vault. The Clanker team burned these tokens earlier today, reducing the circulating supply of each.

3. The Clanker team has also permanently locked roughly 7% of the $CLANKER supply into a one-sided LP to provide additional liquidity, further reducing circulating supply.

FAQ in the next cast.

Clanker was only possible because of Farcaster. 

Its wires are deeply rooted in the open social graph and flourishing ecosystem of developers, traders, creators, and community.

We‚Äôre ecstatic to plant ourselves as a permanent pillar of the Farcaster network and continue to build out the best token deployment framework possible. 

To the Clanker community, thank you for your unwavering support! The best is yet to come.

CLANK CLANK

show_title: Clanker Gets Acquired, Memes Get Unleashed: GM Farcaster ep303 with @dwr and @dish
text:
fwiw, couldn't agree more with dan. sad, but true.

1. i spent most of last year experimenting with URL to IRL and social connection; it doesn't scale OR you need an entire product team focused on it (think 222, rodeo, timeleft, partiful or luma, etc.) and even then it is still a HUGE risk with slow growth.

2. farcaster is mostly crypto users and has crypto primitives (wallet, coins), but the average person doesn't want to hang out on a crypto social network so >half the existing content and exciting features don't make sense to them. this impacts user acquisition and drives churn.

3. rewarding content with $$ is simply not sufficient to attract new users and have them retain at scale; this was immediately obvious after onboarding the journalists or college students and experimenting with the creator rewards. increasing rewards, improving video UX, etc. was never going to change that.

4. my creator/user onboarding was hand-to-hand combat and the common denominator across the most successful onboarded users was the effort or attention dan, linda or i gave to the relationship; again, not scaleable.

leaning into the wallet and tokens is the single greatest decision farcaster has made (outside of its permissionless primitives) to support growth and i fully endorse it, even if it isn't the vision i initially signed up for.

in fact, i wish the decision to let go of creators / content / connection and instead lean into crypto happened sooner.

text:
29 Seconds of Farcaster ... What did you miss this weekend?

What a weekend! If you are new here, I feel bad for you trying to follow along. Give it another few days. 

I probably should've called this 37 Seconds of Farcaster....

* Yes, 37 is everywhere! I guess it started with @tldr wearing his 37 hat, created by @atown ,  to Dev Day & several posting it. But then @tryemerge took over and slammed the timeline. Then @martin created $37 coin. And well, now we just have a crazy 37 playpen. And chris dixon thinks new tech starts as a toy before it gets serious! smh (If you are new, 37 is a 'meme' or joke about FC being small and only having 37 users. /gmfarcaster will expain it further today, I'm sure.

* Speaking of crazy...Dan went unhinged with his Masters of The Warplet Universe creations to @linda 's horror & @horsefacts.eth delight...but it clearly didn't stop there as @sayangel ran with it creating 'Warplets' last night that are, well, um, ugly cute? They are filling the timeline, and those of us who aren't degens and up at all hours are waiting for a chance to mint ours today. 

* In the midst of these shenanigans that might /gmfarcaster shenanigans look mild, there were some more based building moments and discussions. Highly recommend reading the reviews from Dev Day in the comments or quoted here: https://farcaster.xyz/dwr/0xa783d484

* Fantastic convo about the wallet led focus of FC...I'll link you to @ted 's comment to start: https://farcaster.xyz/ted/0x08dc9f29

* /gmfarcaster is on at 10 AM EST (special time) for news and catch up and then at 11 AM EST @dwr & @dish will be on to talk all things $CLANKER which, oh yeah, was also a big topic this weekend in the midst of the fun. @adrienne & @nounishprof have their work cut out for them today, but guaranteed to be a banger of a show!

show_title: Clanker Gets Acquired, Memes Get Unleashed: GM Farcaster ep303 with @dwr and @dish
text:
Great example of the power of Farcaster developer legos

1. @sayangel builds a mini app that pulls in your FID and pfp and remixes it with the Warplet mascot

2. Charge a small mint fee which burns a Clanker token.

3. Share back in the feed for viral distribution. 

4. NFTs show up on OpenSea immediately.

5. The Clanker $WARP benefits from the virality of the meme, the increased eyeballs on the Clanker get people interested in the NFT collection, a floor appears on the NFTs driving more people back into the Farcaster app since you need an FID to mint. 

Discover. Trade. Create.
